dc_description_s: This layer is a georeferenced raster image of the historic paper map entitled: Grund-Riss der Keyserlichen und des Heil. RÃ¶m. Reichs freyen stadt LÃ¼beck, herausgegeben von Matth. Seutter, kayserl. Geogr. It was published by M. Seutter between 1730 and 1739. Covers LÃ¼beck, Germany. Scale [ca. 1:5,600]. Map in German. The image inside the map neatline is georeferenced to the surface of the earth and fit to the Deutsches Hauptdreiecksnetz (DHDN) 3-degree Gauss-Kruger Zone 4 coordinate system. All map collar and inset information is also available as part of the raster image, including any inset maps, profiles, statistical tables, directories, text, illustrations, index maps, legends, or other information associated with the principal map. This map shows features such as roads, drainage, built-up areas and selected buildings, fortifications, ground cover, and more. Includes indexes, illustrations, and a view. This layer is part of a selection of digitally scanned and georeferenced historic maps from the Harvard Map Collection. These maps typically portray both natural and manmade features. The selection represents a range of originators, ground condition dates, scales, and map purposes.
